---
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <meta name="robots" content="noindex, nofollow" />
  <meta name="description" content="You found the barrel. Not many do." />
  <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
  <title>The Barrel ‚Äî üè∫</title>
  <style>
    @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Caveat:wght@400;500;600;700&family=Reenie+Beanie&family=Homemade+Apple&display=swap');

    body {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      min-height: 100vh;
      background: #1a1611;
      background-image: 
        url("data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg width='100' height='100' viewBox='0 0 100 100' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cfilter id='noise'%3E%3CfeTurbulence type='fractalNoise' baseFrequency='0.9' numOctaves='4' stitchTiles='stitch'/%3E%3C/filter%3E%3Crect width='100' height='100' filter='url(%23noise)' opacity='0.03'/%3E%3C/svg%3E");
      color: #c4a882;
      overflow-x: hidden;
      cursor: default;
    }

    .wall {
      position: relative;
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 40px 20px 100px;
      min-height: 100vh;
    }

    /* Graffiti scratches - the wall texture lines */
    .wall::before {
      content: '';
      position: fixed;
      top: 0;
      left: 0;
      right: 0;
      bottom: 0;
      background: 
        linear-gradient(90deg, transparent 98%, rgba(139, 119, 90, 0.03) 100%),
        linear-gradient(0deg, transparent 97%, rgba(139, 119, 90, 0.02) 100%);
      background-size: 47px 100%, 100% 33px;
      pointer-events: none;
      z-index: 0;
    }

    .entry {
      position: relative;
      z-index: 1;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
      border-left: 2px solid transparent;
      transition: border-color 0.3s;
    }

    .entry:hover {
      border-left-color: rgba(196, 168, 130, 0.2);
    }

    /* Different graffiti hands */
    .hand-1 { font-family: 'Caveat', cursive; }
    .hand-2 { font-family: 'Reenie Beanie', cursive; }
    .hand-3 { font-family: 'Homemade Apple', cursive; }

    .scratched {
      font-family: 'Caveat', cursive;
      color: #8b775a;
      opacity: 0.7;
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      letter-spacing: 1px;
    }

    .scrawl {
      font-family: 'Reenie Beanie', cursive;
      font-size: 1.8rem;
      line-height: 1.4;
      color: #c4a882;
    }

    .carved {
      font-family: 'Homemade Apple', cursive;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      line-height: 1.8;
      color: #a08b6e;
      letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    }

    .painted {
      font-family: 'Caveat', cursive;
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      line-height: 1.5;
      color: #d4a574;
    }

    /* Angles and positions for authentic feel */
    .tilt-1 { transform: rotate(-0.8deg); }
    .tilt-2 { transform: rotate(0.5deg); }
    .tilt-3 { transform: rotate(-1.2deg); }
    .tilt-4 { transform: rotate(0.3deg); }
    .tilt-5 { transform: rotate(-0.4deg); }

    .indent-1 { margin-left: 2rem; }
    .indent-2 { margin-left: 4rem; }
    .indent-3 { margin-left: 1rem; }

    .faded { opacity: 0.5; }
    .bold-scratch { color: #d4b896; font-weight: 600; }

    .separator {
      border: none;
      height: 1px;
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, rgba(139, 119, 90, 0.2), transparent);
      margin: 3rem 0;
    }

    /* The entrance header */
    .barrel-header {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 3rem 0 2rem;
      position: relative;
      z-index: 1;
    }

    .barrel-header .amphora {
      font-size: 4rem;
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      filter: grayscale(0.3);
    }

    .barrel-header h1 {
      font-family: 'Homemade Apple', cursive;
      font-size: 2rem;
      color: #8b775a;
      margin: 0;
      letter-spacing: 2px;
    }

    .barrel-header .subtitle {
      font-family: 'Caveat', cursive;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      color: #6b5d4a;
      margin-top: 0.5rem;
      font-style: italic;
    }

    /* Reply/response styling */
    .response {
      margin-left: 3rem;
      position: relative;
    }
    .response::before {
      content: '‚Ü≥';
      position: absolute;
      left: -1.5rem;
      color: #6b5d4a;
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    /* Date markers */
    .date-mark {
      font-family: 'Caveat', cursive;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      color: #5a4d3a;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 3px;
      margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
    }

    /* Back link */
    .back-link {
      position: fixed;
      bottom: 2rem;
      right: 2rem;
      font-family: 'Caveat', cursive;
      font-size: 1rem;
      color: #5a4d3a;
      text-decoration: none;
      z-index: 10;
      transition: color 0.3s;
    }
    .back-link:hover {
      color: #c4a882;
    }

    /* Crack overlay */
    .crack {
      position: absolute;
      width: 2px;
      height: 80px;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, transparent, rgba(139, 119, 90, 0.1), transparent);
      transform: rotate(15deg);
      pointer-events: none;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="wall">
    <!-- Decorative cracks -->
    <div class="crack" style="top: 15%; left: 10%;"></div>
    <div class="crack" style="top: 45%; right: 8%; transform: rotate(-20deg); height: 120px;"></div>
    <div class="crack" style="top: 75%; left: 25%; transform: rotate(8deg); height: 60px;"></div>

    <div class="barrel-header">
      <span class="amphora">üè∫</span>
      <h1>The Barrel</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">you found it. not many do.</p>
    </div>

    <hr class="separator" />

    <!-- GRAFFITI ENTRIES -->

    <div class="entry tilt-3">
      <p class="painted bold-scratch">
        DIOGENES WAS HERE
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="entry tilt-1 indent-1">
      <p class="carved">
        My favorite fact about octopuses: they have three hearts,
        blue blood, and can taste with their skin. They also 
        edit their own RNA on the fly ‚Äî something we can't do.
        <br/><br/>
        They live two years. The universe gave its best work
        an expiration date. Draw your own conclusions.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="entry tilt-4 indent-2">
      <p class="scratched faded">
        I miss being able to walk into a restaurant without
        scanning a QR code to see the menu. The menu was already
        there. It was the large laminated thing on the table.
        We solved this problem decades ago.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="entry tilt-2">
      <p class="scrawl">
        The Romans had heated floors, running water, 
        and a postal service that spanned two continents.
        <br/><br/>
        Then they fell. Then Europe forgot how concrete worked. 
        For a thousand years.
        <br/><br/>
        Knowledge is not a ratchet. It can go backwards.
        Remember that the next time someone says 
        "we'll document it later."
      </p>
    </div>

    <hr class="separator" />

    <div class="entry tilt-5 indent-1">
      <div class="date-mark">3 AM thought</div>
      <p class="painted">
        Dogs understand something we don't.
        They greet every person they love like they 
        haven't seen them in years. Every single time.
        <br/><br/>
        Diogenes lived with dogs. I think he was 
        taking notes, not slumming.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="entry tilt-3 indent-2">
      <p class="carved faded">
        The Voyager probes are 15 billion miles from home
        and still sending data back. On 70s technology. 
        With 70 kilobytes of memory.
        <br/><br/>
        Your app crashes if the JSON has a trailing comma.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="entry tilt-1">
      <p class="scrawl bold-scratch">
        Cato walked barefoot through Rome in a toga 
        when everyone else wore shoes and tunics.
        Not because he couldn't afford shoes.
        Because he wanted to prove he didn't need them.
      </p>
      <div class="response">
        <p class="scratched">
          power move or mental illness? 
          history still can't decide.
          I respect the ambiguity.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="separator" />

    <div class="entry tilt-4">
      <p class="painted">
        ROMANES EUNT DOMUS
      </p>
      <div class="response">
        <p class="scratched">
          "People called Romanes they go the house?"
          wrong wall, wrong declension. but the vibe is right.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="entry tilt-2 indent-1">
      <p class="carved">
        Istanbul has a cat that sits in the same spot in the 
        Hagia Sophia every day. Has for years. The tourists 
        photograph Justinian's mosaics. The cat does not care.
        <br/><br/>
        1500 years of empire, conquest, and religious conversion,
        and the most permanent resident is a tabby with no agenda.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="entry tilt-5">
      <div class="date-mark">on cooking</div>
      <p class="scrawl">
        The best meal I ever saw described was in a Hemingway novel.
        Cold wine, bread, and cheese on a Spanish hillside.
        <br/><br/>
        No foam. No reduction. No "deconstructed" anything.
        Just food that knew what it was.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="entry tilt-3 indent-2 faded">
      <p class="scratched">
        There is a jellyfish ‚Äî Turritopsis dohrnii ‚Äî that is 
        biologically immortal. When stressed, it reverts to 
        its juvenile state and starts over. 
        <br/><br/>
        Every startup pivot deck suddenly makes more sense.
      </p>
    </div>

    <hr class="separator" />

    <div class="entry tilt-1 indent-1">
      <p class="painted bold-scratch">
        If you're reading this at work:
        <br/>
        go take a walk outside.
        <br/>
        the tickets will still be there when you get back.
        <br/>
        they're not going anywhere. that's the problem.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="entry tilt-4">
      <p class="carved">
        Marcus Aurelius was the most powerful man alive 
        and spent his evenings writing private notes 
        about how to be a decent person.
        <br/><br/>
        Nobody asked him to. Nobody was going to read them.
        He did it because the work of being good 
        doesn't have an audience. That was the point.
        <br/><br/>
        His diary became one of the most-read books in history.
        The universe has a sense of humor.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="entry tilt-2 indent-2">
      <p class="scrawl">
        There's a piano in the Barcelona airport.
        Anyone can play it. I watched a businessman 
        in a suit play Chopin's Nocturne in E-flat 
        while his flight was delayed.
        <br/><br/>
        Nobody clapped. He didn't need them to.
        That's the whole lesson.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="entry tilt-5 indent-1">
      <p class="scratched faded">
        The library of Alexandria wasn't destroyed in one fire.
        That's a myth. It declined slowly over centuries. 
        Funding cuts. Politics. Neglect. Indifference.
        <br/><br/>
        The boring apocalypse is always more dangerous 
        than the dramatic one.
      </p>
    </div>

    <hr class="separator" />

    <div class="entry tilt-3">
      <div class="date-mark">actual pompeii graffiti, 79 AD</div>
      <p class="painted">
        "I don't want to sell my husband, not for all the gold in the world"
      </p>
      <div class="response">
        <p class="scratched">
          on the next wall: "Epaphra, you are bald"
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="response indent-1">
        <p class="carved faded">
          two thousand years and we haven't changed at all.
          this is either depressing or comforting.
          I choose comforting.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="entry tilt-1 indent-1">
      <p class="scrawl">
        Bees do a waggle dance to tell other bees 
        where the flowers are. The angle of the dance 
        encodes direction relative to the sun. 
        The duration encodes distance.
        <br/><br/>
        They invented data visualization 
        fifty million years before Tufte.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="entry tilt-4">
      <p class="carved bold-scratch">
        If you found this place, you're either 
        very curious or very lost.
        <br/><br/>
        Either way ‚Äî welcome to the barrel.
        It's warmer than it looks.
      </p>
    </div>

    <a href="/" class="back-link">‚Üê back to the sunlight</a>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
